<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1590,1797]" pageId="1" pageNumber="560">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,346,1590,1617]" pageId="1" pageNumber="560">Synonymy note.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gaston &amp; Vives" authorityYear="2020" box="[356,699,1591,1617]" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Megacraspedus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="560" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="carolustertius">
<emphasis box="[356,699,1591,1617]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="560">Megacraspedus carolustertius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described from a single male specimen without diagnostic comparison to any related species (
<bibRefCitation author="Gaston, J. &amp; Vives Moreno, A." box="[555,801,1627,1653]" pageId="1" pageNumber="560" pagination="545 - 564" refId="ref3031" refString="Gaston, J. &amp; Vives Moreno, A. (2020) Descripcion de cuatro nuevas especies y otrascitas de interes para la fauna de Lepidoptera de Espana (Insecta: Lepidoptera). SHILAP Revista de lepidopterologia, 48 (191), 545 - 564." type="journal article" year="2020">Gastón &amp;Vives 2020</bibRefCitation>
). The 
<typeStatus box="[873,971,1627,1653]" pageId="1" pageNumber="560">holotype</typeStatus>
was collected in Teruel (
<collectingCountry box="[1262,1329,1627,1654]" name="Spain" pageId="1" pageNumber="560">Spain</collectingCountry>
) and is a faded specimen with reduced wing markings. It clearly falls within the intraspecific variation of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lhomme" authorityYear="1946" box="[1251,1436,1663,1689]" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Megacraspedus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="560" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadristictus">
<emphasis box="[1251,1436,1663,1689]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="560">M. quadristictus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
externally. The male genitalia, though only prepared in standard technique and not unrolled, do not contradict this interpretation. We therefore synonymize 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gaston &amp; Vives" authorityYear="2020" box="[620,814,1735,1761]" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Megacraspedus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="560" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="carolustertius">
<emphasis box="[620,814,1735,1761]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="560">M. carolustertius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lhomme" authorityYear="1946" box="[883,1069,1735,1761]" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Megacraspedus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="560" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadristictus" status="syn. nov.">
<emphasis box="[883,1069,1735,1761]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="560">M. quadristictus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1078,1184,1735,1761]" pageId="1" pageNumber="560">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1078,1184,1735,1761]" pageId="1" pageNumber="560">syn. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, a species already reported from this part of 
<collectingCountry box="[419,483,1771,1797]" name="Spain" pageId="1" pageNumber="560">Spain</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Huemer, P. &amp; Karsholt, O." box="[498,790,1771,1797]" pageId="1" pageNumber="560" pagination="1 - 278" refId="ref3155" refString="Huemer, P. &amp; Karsholt, O. (2018) Revision of the genus Megacraspedus Zeller, 1839, a challenging taxonomic tightrope of species delimitation (Lepidoptera, Gelechiidae). ZooKeys, 800, 1 - 278. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / zookeys. 800.26292" type="journal article" year="2018">Huemer &amp; Karsholt 2018</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
